data: Ethan M. Dolle Ethan M. Dolle Senior Lecturer Ethan.Dolle@nau.edu 928-523-9248 19-213 Research/teaching: Dr. Dolle’s research interests include dark matter, general relativity, and physics beyond the standard model. In the classroom, he utilizes active learning strategies and peer instruction techniques to maximize student performance. Dr. Dolle also partners with the Center for Science Teaching and Learning and the Coconino County Education Service Agency to create and present materials for K12 professional development workshops. PhD, Physics, University of Arizona BS, Physics and Astronomy, University of Arizona
